  "body": "Dar Global and FENDI Casa have launched Azure Oceanfront Villas, a collection of 19 ultra-luxury mansions with direct beach access within the AIDA clifftop community in Muscat, Oman. The unveiling represents a significant milestone for Oman as Azure Oceanfront Villas becomes the first development in the Sultanate to feature interiors by the design brand of a luxury fashion Maison. It is also the first residential collaboration between the London-listed developer and the Italian design house.\n\nThe 19 mansions are built on a 130-metre-high cliff, surrounded by rocky canyons, pristine beaches, and the scenic Oman coastline. Each villa offers four or five bedrooms, private pools, private lifts, and uninterrupted Indian Ocean views. With spacious floor plans, each villa includes private amenities such as an outdoor pool and a state-of-the-art gym. Beautifully furnished, the homes reflect FENDI Casa's renowned blend of elegance and contemporary style, with curated attention to details, materials, and artisanal craftsmanship. Completion is scheduled for December 2028.\n\nThe launch underscores the structural shift in Oman's luxury residential mandate. Oman's luxury property sector is at a turning point, fuelled by investor appetite for branded residences and government initiatives driving inbound investment; the partnership with FENDI Casa brings world-renowned Italian design to this vision, elevating the standard of upscale living in Muscat. In June, Whitewill recorded an OMR 1.74 million ($4.53 million) Fendi Casa Villa sale at AIDA, one of the highest-value villa transactions within the development. That transaction—prior to today's formal launch—signals pre-sale absorption among international buyers seeking design-led distinction and lifestyle-led amenities.\n\nZiad El Chaar, CEO of Dar Global, framed the release within the developer's growth-market thesis. \"The launch of Azure Oceanfront Villas, Interiors by FENDI Casa, at AIDA reflects Dar Global's commitment to identifying and unlocking high-value real estate opportunities in growth markets,\" he said, adding that \"together, we are further elevating the position of AIDA as a strategic gateway for global investors seeking long-term value, lifestyle returns, and design-led distinction in the region.\"\n\nAIDA spans over 4.3 million square metres and targets international investors and buyers, blending nature, luxury, and lifestyle with world-class hotels, an 18-hole golf course, an exclusive members-only club, and a bouquet of residential offerings including upscale villas and apartments. Centrally located in the Omani capital, within a short distance of Muscat International Airport and Central Downtown, this significant urban development in Oman is enhancing the country's global stature as a compelling destination for tourists, residents, and investors alike. Spanning 4.3 million sqm at 130 metres above the Indian Ocean, AIDA features an 18-hole golf course, Nikki Beach Resort & Spa, beaches, and world-class amenities.\n\nThe broader AIDA masterplan is a joint venture between Dar Global and Omran Group, Oman's sovereign tourism-development entity. With the first phase of the AIDA project, including critical infrastructure, set for completion by 2027, investors are poised to benefit from early entry into a rapidly maturing luxury destination. Spanning 5 million square metres and situated just 10 minutes from Downtown Muscat, AIDA aims to redefine standards in architectural excellence, environmental sustainability, and bespoke living. (Note: sources cite both 4.3 million and 5 million square metres; the discrepancy likely reflects different measurement methodologies or phasing.)\n\nPricing across AIDA's villa typologies varies by configuration and view orientation. AIDA offers 3-bedroom Attached Villas starting from AED 2,463,805, 4-bedroom Villas from AED 4,687,044, and 5-bedroom Villas from AED 6,166,285. Clifftop residences at AIDA start from 117,000 OMR. Flexible 5-year payment plans are available, with properties at AIDA offering payment plans spread over 5 years, with an initial deposit and staged payments tied to construction. The payment plan for AIDA involves 20% payment on booking, 50% payment during construction, and the remaining 30% payment upon handover.\n\nThe Azure Oceanfront Villas sit within a zero-tax jurisdiction that has become a catalyst for UHNW capital rotation. Oman has 0% personal income tax, 0% capital gains tax, and 0% inheritance tax; there is no tax on rental income for individual investors—making Oman one of the most tax-efficient property markets in the world. Prime residential properties in Muscat typically generate 6–8% annual rental yields; at AIDA, the clifftop location, resort amenities, and managed rental programme support strong consistent returns. Oman residency is included with qualifying purchases.\n\nDar Global has partnered with over ten luxury brands to deliver branded residential product across nine countries. DarGlobal has partnered with over 10 world-renowned luxury brands, including Trump Organization, Aston Martin, Automobili Lamborghini, Fendi, ELIE SAAB, Marriott Residences, Missoni, Mouawad, Pagani Automobili, and W Hotels. With a presence in 14 international cities across 9 countries, DarGlobal's portfolio, encompassing 4,200 units completed and under construction, spans the United Kingdom, Spain, Greece, Saudi Arabia, the UAE, Oman, and Qatar. Listed on the London Stock Exchange, DarGlobal goes beyond property development—it drives economic transformation by attracting international clients and Foreign Direct Investment (FDI).\n\nFounded in 1987 as a pioneering expression of the FENDI vision of living, FENDI Casa is today developed by Luxury Living Group, the leading company in the field of design, production, and distribution of luxury furnishings for several of the most prominent international brands and is part of Haworth Lifestyle group. The Azure Oceanfront Villas mark FENDI Casa's first foray into the Omani market and its first high-end residential project with Dar Global.\n\nThe launch arrives as Oman accelerates its Vision 2040 diversification mandate, targeting tourism and real estate as structural GDP contributors. This strategic investment aligns with Oman's Vision 2040, which aims to significantly develop the country's tourism sector and contribute to GDP growth. The convergence of sovereign backing, zero-tax treatment, and branded-residence scarcity positions AIDA—and the Azure Oceanfront Villas within it—as a test case for whether fashion-house interiors can command a sustained premium in a frontier GCC market. Early transaction velocity suggests the thesis is holding.",
